o calculate their exact durations.\n\nThe ed2d0b5d cron session started at 18:24:18 UTC, so it's been running for about 50 minutes and 50 seconds. The 6f3323ef cron session started at 18:23:56 UTC and has been running for approximately 61 minutes and 12 seconds. I'll format these durations nicely and compile the final report with the session names, statuses, and task descriptions.\n\nFor the telegram:group session, there's a discrepancy—the session ended at 17:42:03 UTC according to the metadata, but the updatedAt timestamp suggests it was last active much more recently at 18:21:53 UTC. Looking at the recent message activity, there's a heartbeat message that arrived at 18:15:03 UTC, so the session is actually still running despite what the endedAt field indicates. I'll include it in the report but note that it's zombie/stale data. For the telegram:direct session, it ended around 18:02 UTC.\n\nNow I'm checking the status field for the 5p QLHV session—it's showing as \"running\" in the status field, which is unusual since there's an endedAt timestamp. But given that the status explicitly says running and it's a heartbeat monitor that might report endedAt on each cycle, I'm treating it as active. The main heartbeat session is done and belongs to a different cron job. So I have three cron sessions to report: the 5p QLHV Progress Report (ed2d0b5d), the 5p DTLX Progress Report (6f3323ef), and the Agent Status to Lead session (e7885813), which has a zombie status noted. The telegram:group is running with the last message from 18:15 UTC, and the telegram:direct session ended at 18:02 UTC. Excluding the cron session itself, that's 3 active cron jobs plus 2 telegram sessions, so I'm sending a full report to Lead. I'm calculating the exact durations for each session—the 5p QLHV and Agent Status sessions are both running around 51 minutes, while the DTLX one is at about 61 minutes—and now I'll send this to the Lead's Telegram session.","thinkingSignature":"c61f51615234845a0f46e